         <abstract id="aspace_e7100827b55366db68969ce9b270a629">Detailed correspondence, diaries, photographs, and collected material document the life and work of a young, single woman missionary in China. Elsie Clark Krug was an American Methodist missionary in Foochow from 1912 to 1918. She taught at Hwa Nan College, then in its preliminary stages a mission-supported college for women.</abstract>
